  <main id="main">
   <header class="hero">
    <h1>
     [FR]: 🚨 Emergency Triage
    </h1>
    <p>
     [FR]: Fast navigator for the first moments of an emergency. It is not a diagnosis: choose the closest match, call your local emergency number for life-threatening symptoms, and follow dispatcher/local guidance.
    </p>
   </header>
   <section>
    <div class="box warn">
     <strong>
      [FR]: If the scene is unsafe
     </strong>
     [FR]: — move yourself away from fire, traffic, violence, electrical hazards, chemicals, smoke, or other danger if you can. Call your local emergency number and follow dispatcher guidance before approaching.
    </div>
    <div class="box emergency">
     <strong>
      [FR]: If someone is unconscious and not breathing normally
     </strong>
     🚨[REVIEW_REQUIRED] [FR]: — gasping or not breathing at all — call your local emergency number, put the phone on speaker, send someone for an AED if available, and start CPR immediately.
     <br/>
     <br/>
     <a class="btn" href="../cpr/">
      [FR]: Open CPR guide →
     </a>
    </div>
   </section>
   <section>
    <h2>
     [FR]: What do you see?
    </h2>
    <div class="two">
     <div class="box">
      <h3>
       [FR]: 😮 Can't breathe, speak, or cough
      </h3>
      <p>
       [FR]: Person is clutching their throat, turning blue, or making high-pitched sounds.
      </p>
      <a class="btn alt" href="../choking/">
       [FR]: Choking guide →
      </a>
     </div>
     <div class="box emergency">
      <h3>
       [FR]: 🩸 Heavy bleeding
      </h3>
      <p>
       [FR]: Blood is spurting, pooling, soaking through bandages, or the limb is severed.
      </p>
      <a class="btn" href="../bleeding/">
       [FR]: Severe Bleeding guide →
      </a>
     </div>
     <div class="box">
      <h3>
       [FR]: 🧠 Sudden face droop, arm weakness, slurred speech
      </h3>
      <p>
       [FR]: Or sudden severe headache, confusion, trouble seeing, or loss of balance.
      </p>
      <a class="btn alt" href="../stroke/">
       [FR]: Stroke guide →
      </a>
     </div>
     <div class="box">
      <h3>
       [FR]: 💊 Cannot wake, slow or abnormal breathing after possible opioid use
      </h3>
      <p>
       🚨[REVIEW_REQUIRED] [FR]: Possible opioid overdose. Call emergency services, give naloxone if available, and support breathing/follow dispatcher guidance.
      </p>
      <a class="btn alt" href="../naloxone/">
       [FR]: Opioid Overdose guide →
      </a>
     </div>
     <div class="box warn">
      <h3>
       [FR]: 🥵 Confusion, fainting, very hot skin
      </h3>
      <p>
       [FR]: In hot weather or after exertion. Could be heat stroke.
      </p>
      <a class="btn alt" href="../heat/">
       [FR]: Extreme Heat guide →
      </a>
     </div>
     <div class="box warn">
      <h3>
       [FR]: 🌫️ Coughing, chest tightness, smoky air
      </h3>
      <p>
       [FR]: During a wildfire or heavy air pollution. Vulnerable people at highest risk.
      </p>
      <a class="btn alt" href="../smoke/">
       [FR]: Wildfire Smoke guide →
      </a>
     </div>
     <div class="box ok">
      <h3>
       [FR]: 💧 Vomiting, diarrhea, very thirsty, dark urine
      </h3>
      <p>
       [FR]: Signs of dehydration. Especially dangerous for children and older adults.
      </p>
      <a class="btn alt" href="../ors/">
       [FR]: Dehydration &amp; ORS guide →
      </a>
     </div>
     <div class="box emergency">
      <h3>
       [FR]: 🐝 Trouble breathing, swelling, or faintness after allergen exposure
      </h3>
      <p>
       🚨[REVIEW_REQUIRED] [FR]: Possible anaphylaxis: call emergency services, use epinephrine if indicated by an action plan/product/local responder rules, and position safely.
      </p>
      <a class="btn" href="../allergy/">
       [FR]: Severe Allergy guide →
      </a>
     </div>
     <div class="box">
      <h3>
       [FR]: 🔥 Burn from fire, hot liquid, or chemical
      </h3>
      <p>
       🚨[REVIEW_REQUIRED] [FR]: Cool under running water for 20 minutes if possible, cover loosely, and do not use ice or home remedies.
      </p>
      <a class="btn alt" href="../burns/">
       [FR]: Burns guide →
      </a>
     </div>
     <div class="box">
      <h3>
       [FR]: ⚡ Rigid jerking, loss of consciousness
      </h3>
      <p>
       [FR]: Seizure. Protect the head, time it, do not restrain or put anything in the mouth.
      </p>
      <a class="btn alt" href="../seizure/">
       [FR]: Seizure guide →
      </a>
     </div>
    </div>
   </section>
   <section>
    <div class="box">
     <h3>
      [FR]: General first steps for any emergency
     </h3>
     <ol class="steps">
      <li>
       <strong>
        [FR]: Check safety.
       </strong>
       [FR]: If unsafe, move away and call for help before approaching.
      </li>
      <li>
       <strong>
        [FR]: Check responsiveness.
       </strong>
       [FR]: Tap their shoulder and shout. No response + not breathing normally → CPR.
      </li>
      <li>
       <strong>
        [FR]: Call for help.
       </strong>
       [FR]: Call your local emergency number. Put the phone on speaker so the dispatcher can guide you.
      </li>
      <li>
       <strong>
        [FR]: Use the guide above
       </strong>
       [FR]: that matches what you see, while following dispatcher/local guidance.
      </li>
     </ol>
    </div>
   </section>
   <section class="disclaimer">
    <p>
     [FR]: This navigator is not a diagnosis and is not a substitute for first-aid training. When in doubt about a serious or rapidly worsening symptom, call your local emergency number. Verify guidance against your local health authority.
    </p>
    <p>
     [FR]: Reuse and reprint freely.
     <a href="../localize.html">
      [FR]: Localize before sharing
     </a>
     .
    </p>
   </section>
